  "local_port": 58762,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I check my last 3 charges in Vodafone?",
  "response": "To check your last 3 charges with Vodafone, you can follow these steps:\n\n### Via the Vodafone App:\n1. **Download and Open the Vodafone App**: Make sure you have the Vodafone app installed on your smartphone. If not, download it from the App Store or Google Play Store.\n2. **Log In**: Use your Vodafone account credentials to log in.\n3. **Navigate to Billing**: Look for a section labeled \"Billing,\" \"Account,\" or \"Usage.\"\n4. **View Recent Charges**: Within the billing section, you should find an option to view your recent charges or billing history. Select this to see your last 3 charges.\n\n### Via the Vodafone Website:\n1. **Visit the Vodafone Website**: Go to the Vodafone website for your country (e.g., www.vodafone.co.uk for the UK).\n2. **Log In**: Enter your Vodafone account details to log in.\n3. **Go to My Account/Billing**: Find and click on the \"My Account\" or \"Billing\" section.\n4. **Check Billing History**: Look for an option to view your billing history or recent charges. This should list your last 3 charges.\n\n### Via Customer Service:\n1. **Call Customer Service**: Dial the Vodafone customer service number for your country.\n2. **Provide Your Details**: Give your account information to the customer service representative.\n3. **Request Billing History**: Ask them to provide you with the details of your last 3 charges.\n\n### Via Text/SMS (if available in your country):\n1. **Send a Text**: Some countries allow you to text a specific number or keyword to get billing information. Check Vodafone's website or your plan details for the correct SMS code.\n2. **Receive a Response**: You should get a reply with your recent charges.\n\nMake sure you have your account details handy, as you may need them to access this information. If you encounter any issues, reaching out to Vodafone customer service directly would be the best course of action.",
